<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tehuantepecensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea tehuantepecensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in habit, corolla shape and in the reddish sepals but immediately distinguished by the sericeous exterior of the corolla and sepals. Also resembles 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="conzattii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea conzattii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in the much shorter corolla lobes and the sericeous corolla.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
